AMIGA

•	What year was it made? 1985
•	What operating system does it run? AmigaOS
•	How much did it cost (then and now, adjusted for inflation)? How hard is it to find one on the secondhand market (check eBay and Craig’s List). In 1985, the Amiga sold for $1,595 ($3,500 price adjusted for inflation).  Of all of the platforms available today through secondhand markets, the Amiga may be the most difficult to find.  There are a few listed on eBay, though the price varies significantly with prices listed from $500 to $5,000.
•	In brief (a short paragraph), what were its historical strengths and weaknesses as a platform? What was it best known for?


